title: For Sale:  LC Smith Quality A-1 - RARE 16 Gauge, 1 OF 10 MADE FIGURED ENGLISH WALNUT, 28” DAMASCUS
postcontent: The Quality A-1 was a very handsome sidelock ejector gun with a relatively short production run that lasted from 1892 to 1898.  During that period a total of only 752 A-1 guns were made; 29 in 10ga., 713 in 12ga., and 10 total made in 16ga.  They only offered the 16ga. in the final 2 years of production, hence the extremely low production.   The Quality A-1 can be found with several engraving patterns, most fairly sparse in coverage.  The “early style” engraving pattern was by far the most elaborate and desirable.  The frames were gracefully sculpted, with shaping very refined and indicative of a finely made best gun.  This gun, sn4151 made in 1898, is graced with the very detailed “early style” engraving and is in very nice factory original condition…only the wood has seen some finish applied over the years and a new pad has been installed.  What a great find, with modern shootable dimensions, fine chain Damascus barrels with perfect mirror bores, 30 thousandths minimum wall thickness anywhere on either barrel, no cracks or repairs in the buttstock, gorgeous, highly figured English walnut with perfect 28LPI checkering (we can restore the wood with a perfect hand rubbed oil finish, removing all nicks and dings, for $400 within 8 weeks of purchase…the wood would really “pop” if done, but we wanted that to be up to the new owner), mechanically excellent with perfectly timed ejectors, solid 3 position auto-safety, a great gun all around.  This is not just a collector gun.  It is fully capable of shooting the 1 ounce 16ga. loads at upland birds or clay targets and is choked Cyl/LM for excellent upland capabilities.  THIS GUN IS THE DEFINITION OF RARE AND SHOULD BE IN ANY AVID L.C. SMITH COLLECTORS GUN CASE.  If you like the guns restored, we can provide that service to historical perfection in a very reasonable amount of time.  When they only made 10 of them, this is truly your only chance to own such a fine Elsie.  Don’t let this one get away!  Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  Colt Single Action Army .32 W.C.F. – UNTOUCHED UNTOUCHED FACTORY 90% CONDITION, 1903
postcontent: This is an original pre-WWI First Generation Colt Single Action Army (SAA) Revolver in a .32 W.C.F. caliber (.32-20). The Colt Peacemaker Model 1873 was the mainstay of the Frontier.  This Colt, sn249268 shipped in 1903, is in superb factory original condition, untouched by the restorer’s hands, still retaining 97% strong factory case color, about 85% nice dark factory blue (showing some natural holster wear, but no rust, pits, or remnants of such), a desirable 7 ½” barrel with excellent sharp rifling, clear sharp lettering and stampings, excellent original screws, hard rubber grips original and serial numbered to the gun with just light wear to the checkering, all matching serial numbers…just a delightful, honest example of a fine Colt from the turn of the century.  A factory letter documenting the gun is included in the photos and will accompany the gun upon sale.  The .32-20 was only 8% of the total production of Colt SAA revolvers, so represents a rather rare caliber.  It is also a caliber that interchanged with the Winchester 1892 rifle so that a cowboy could have one batch of cartridges for both rifle and handgun.  The ammunition is still available and a recent gun writer dubbed the .32-20 the first “MAGNUM” .32 caliber cartridge, as it develops impressive speed and ballistics for a smaller caliber SAA.  What a fun gun this would be to shoot some tin cans or jack rabbits with.  Just imagine where this gun has been and the stories it could tell!  The gun was shipped to San Francisco, California in the days there were still cowboys and drifters gambling in the saloon and gunfighting in the streets.  It was likely ordered by a rancher or picked up at the General Store to carry while tending cattle and riding the range.  The mechanics of the gun are excellent, with the timing of the action perfect and no play in the cylinder when cocked.  If case color remaining is the measure of the gun, as some people say, this is a very high condition gun indeed.  I state 90% overall with no excuses.  Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 42 – CUSTOM UPGRADE, ANGELO BEE, RAISED GOLD INLAYS, 3X WOOD winchester m42 .410ga
postcontent: The Model 42 is an icon in the ranks of Winchester firearms, made in the days of the highest quality control and hand fitted parts.  The Model 42 was a flawlessly produced little pump gun, chambered only for the diminutive .410 shotgun shell.  In the 30 years of production that ran from 1933 to 1963, almost 160,000 of these fine guns were produced.  A very large percentage were Field Grade guns, and there were also Skeet Grades, Trap Grades, and the Deluxe Grade.  There were just over 5000 Skeet Grades ever produced, or about 3% of total production.  The Winchester Model 42 has been held dear in the eyes of the .410 aficionado, and there has been a strong following for the upgraded guns that have been highly decorated with fine bank-note scroll, gold inlays, fancy wood, etc.  Angelo Bee is a sought after engraving artist that has been responsible for many of these fine upgrades, and as he winds down his life’s work spanning decades, the attention to his accomplishments is multiplying rapidly.  This beautiful Model 42, sn133879 built in the mid-1950’s, is a grand example of an Angelo Bee custom Winchester M42.  Done in concert with Christophe Rouffose (scroll work), the bank note scroll is deeply carved with shaded backgrounds, beautifully done.  The 4 raised gold doves on the right side of the receiver and 4 raised gold quail on the left side of the receiver is representative of what this gun would excel at in the field; hunting small-framed, thin-skinned game birds.  The wood is fully figured exhibition grade black walnut with perfect 22lpi checkering and perfect hand rubbed oil finish.  This gun is 100% without a mark or ding anywhere in the wood, and only slight wear on the slide action bluing.  What a gorgeous gun to have in your collection and utilize in the field.  These guns are sure to go up in value as Angelo Bee begins to slow down and retire in the next few years.  A great investment vehicle and source of pride and shooting pleasures, a Winchester Model 42 custom built by Angelo Bee is a gun you should have in your collection!  Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:   Beretta ARX 100
postcontent: The ARX100 was engineered with one purpose in mind: to be today’s best tactical semiauto rifle. It takes the concept of a modular rifle to futuristic levels, while maintaining an absolutely simple operation that make it ultra-reliable. With ambidextrous controls, easily-replaceable barrel and virtually endless possibilities for customization and accessorization, the ARX100 is adaptable to any firing scenario and is perfect for today’s most demanding tactical shooter. The ARX100 features a constant contact/short-stroke gas piston system that makes it feed and fire under the most unforgiving conditions. The lightweight techno polymer receiver allows for reliable operation with virtually no lubricants. To make maintenance easy and trouble-free, this rifle has no pins and can be completely disassembled in a matter of seconds with no tools at all. This rifle was designed to be completely ambidextrous, and all the critical controls on it may be operated right- or left-handed. These include the 2-position safety, the magazine release, the bolt release and charging handle and the case-ejection selector, which determines whether spent brass is ejected to the right or left. The flip-up backup sights that come standard on the ARX100 are also versatile, offering an easily-adjustable diopter system ranged from 100 to 800 yards. The barrel is also easily replaceable in seconds, making is possible to use different lengths and calibers without any tools required. Lastly, the folding stock is adjustable for length of pull at the touch of a button, using a simple and rugged telescopic construction. The possibilities for accessorization on the ARX100 are limited only by the user’s imagination. It comes out of the box with a full-length Picatinny rail on top, which is perfect for attaching a variety of optics and other sighting systems. It also has Picatinny rails on both sides of and under the fore-end, which offer countless possibilities for easily adding lighting systems and other tactical devices.
